text: Eivind Vorren Karlsbakk, born 4 May 1975, is a retired footballer from Stryn in Norway. He is most known for his time years in Brann, but has also played for several other Norwegian clubs. In the 1995 Norwegian Football Cup final, Karlsbakk was sent off by the referee Jon E. Skjervold. After reviewing the video replay the referee changed his report and Karlsbakk were allowed to play the re-match the following week. ==References== Category:Norwegian footballers Category:SK Brann players Category:Sogndal Fotball players Category:Living people Category:1975 births Category:People from Stryn Category:Mandalskameratene players Category:Åsane Fotball players Category:Bryne FK players Category:Association football forwards
